    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm trying to learn music theory and im super confused by the circle of fifths. can u explain what it actually is and how i can use it to figure out what key signature a song is in?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The circle of fifths is a visual representation of the relationships among the 12 tones of the chromatic scale. Each step clockwise in the circle of fifths is a perfect fifth higher than the previous key. To find the key signature from a song, look up the cadence or tonic chord closest to the circle of fifths. For example, if the tonic chord is C major, its position in the circle points to the key of C major with no accidentals. As you move away from C major in the circle, you'll encounter more sharps or flats representing the key signatures of other major and minor keys. Practice by identifying key signatures using the circle of fifths, and happy music learning!",
      "source": "target",
